ve condition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnvironmental monitoringxMethodology. 0aIntertidal ecologyxResearchxMethodology. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  abrackish.  aclimate change.  acoastline.  aearth sciences.  aecology.  aenvironment.  aenvironmentalism.  afield sampling layouts.  afieldwork.  aglobal warming.  agrowth rates.  aintertidal macroinvertebrates.  aintertidal zone.  aintertidal.  amacroinvertebrates.  amarine environment.  anature.  anonfiction.  aocean health.  aocean plants.  aocean.  aoceanography.  aquantifying abundance.  areproductive condition.  asampling units.  ascience.  aseagrasses.  aseaweeds.  ashoreline.  asite selection.  awater plants.1 aAmbrose, Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDethier, Megan N., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093271540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520932715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520932715/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles